<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 28 at 7:26PM CDT until May 28 at 8:30PM CDT by NWS Bismarck</headline>
<description>The National Weather Service in Bismarck has issued a
* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Bowman County in southwestern North Dakota...
Western Adams County in southwestern North Dakota...
* Until 730 PM MDT.
* At 625 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 6 miles southwest of Ladner to 8 miles southwest of
Ralph, moving northeast at 45 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
* Locations impacted include...
Bowman, Hettinger and Scranton.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
